Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, season with @salt and @pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}(peeled), then cut each half into 4 wedges.

Add the pepper chunks, onion wedges and @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} to one side of another large baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt and @pepper and toss to coat.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @British chicken thighs{3} and @pesto{32%g}. Season with @salt and @pepper and toss to coat the chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the chicken thighs to the other side of the #baking tray{}.

Roast the chicken and veg on the middle shelf of your oven until the veg has softened and the chicken is slightly golden and cooked through, ~{16-18%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When everything's ready, drizzle the @honey{1%tbsp} and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} over the roasted veg. Toss to coat evenly.

Share the potato chunks and roasted veg between your serving bowls.

Top with the pesto chicken and sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Finish by drizzling over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!